n person" is on the Internet. Having a stand-out, consistent brand is imperative.', 11252, 0), (345579, 'Like it or not, how we each present ourselves to the world, by way of our appearance, attire, behavior, and speech, all send messages on our behalf.', 11252, 0), (345580, 'The first thing others see is YOU—not your resume, background, or credentials. A picture is truly worth a thousand words and how you dress is the “picture” you provide for all the world to see.', 11252, 0), (345581, 'Making a great first impression is not an accident, and with a little planning, experimentation, and application, you can transform your style, substance, and impact.', 11252, 0), (345582, 'The word “brand” has now taken an individualized and highly personalized shift toward how you are perceived in the minds of others.', 11252, 0), (345583, 'Is your branding serving your needs for positive impact? Is it paving the way for a great first impression on people when they meet you, think of you, speak of you, or even see you on the Internet? If not, it’s time for a change, and it is perfectly within your control.', 11252, 0), (345584, 'To help get your creative juices flowing, you might look online at lists of the "best taglines ever." Their branding ideas are genius and may be just the catalyst you need to activate your awesome!', 11252, 0), (345585, 'Dumb luck and flying by the seat of your pants can only get you so far in life.', 11252, 0), (345586, 'Being prepared prevents us from getting tripped up by unexpected glitches and surprises.', 11252, 0), (345587, 'Emotionally intelligent people trust their instincts and can identify how certain thoughts, feelings, people, and situations make them feel.', 11252, 0), (345588, 'Emotionally intelligent people hold themselves accountable for their behavior, failures, decisions, and successes.', 11252, 0), (345589, 'Being prepared not only reduces our stress level and keeps us from looking stupid, but it builds the confidence that other people